<subSubSection id="C3196546FFB8FFE4FF0CEA46B30CEE97" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BBC36CDFFB8FFE4FF0CEA46B30CEE97" blockId="1.[151,1437,375,943]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="B977EADFFFB8FFE4FF0CEA46B122EEB7" bold="true" box="[198,327,631,655]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named in honor of Kirstie L. Kaiser of Puerto Vallarta, 
<collectingCountry id="F314765DFFB8FFE4FC32EA49B429EEB7" box="[1016,1100,632,655]" name="Mexico" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, who greatly assisted in our understanding of offshore island mollusks in the Panamic Province.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3196546FFB8FFE4FF0CEA86B259EF37" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BBC36CDFFB8FFE4FF0CEA86B3B0EEF7" blockId="1.[151,1437,375,943]" box="[198,981,695,719]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="B977EADFFFB8FFE4FF0CEA86B13CEEF7" bold="true" box="[198,345,695,719]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from a single specimen from the 
<typeStatus id="54B8886FFFB8FFE4FC80EA89B31DEEF7" box="[842,888,696,719]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36CDFFB8FFE4FF0CEAE6B259EF37" blockId="1.[151,1437,375,943]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="B977EADFFFB8FFE4FF0CEAE6B101EED7" bold="true" box="[198,356,727,751]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Comparisons.</emphasis>
